  <div class="eyebrow"><div class="eyebrow-dot"></div>Stage 08 — Data Extraction Pipeline</div>
  <div class="h2">URL → Clean Article Text <span>in 5 Steps (With Fallbacks)</span></div>
  <p class="lead">When a user pastes a URL the backend extracts clean article text without paywall bypass. The pipeline tries the best method first and falls back gracefully. Extracted text is cached 1 hour.</p>

  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step"><div class="step-n">0</div><div class="step-body"><div class="step-title">Cache Check — _url_text_cache in-memory dict</div><div class="step-desc">Every extracted article stored in _url_text_cache[url] with _cached_at timestamp. If time.time() − cached_at &lt; 3600, return cached result immediately. Zero HTTP calls, zero scraping, instant response.</div></div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-n">1</div><div class="step-body"><div class="step-title">newspaper4k — Structured Article Parser (2-second hard timeout)</div><div class="step-desc">newspaper.Article(url).download() then .parse() uses ML-based article boundary detection. Runs inside ThreadPoolExecutor with future.result(timeout=2). If &gt;2 seconds, future.cancel() and move to Step 2. Requires &gt;100 chars of extracted text to use result.</div></div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-n">2</div><div class="step-body"><div class="step-title">BeautifulSoup Fallback — HTML Scraper (3-second timeout)</div><div class="step-desc">requests.get(url, timeout=3) with Chrome 120 User-Agent. Parse with html.parser. Strip: script, style, nav, footer, aside, header, iframe, noscript. Find container: &lt;article&gt; → CSS class pattern "article|post|content|story|entry" → full body fallback. Extract first 50 &lt;p&gt; tags &gt;25 chars. Cap at 5000 chars.</div></div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-n">3</div><div class="step-body"><div class="step-title">Title Extraction — 3-level fallback</div><div class="step-desc">Find &lt;h1&gt; in article container → og:title meta → &lt;title&gt; HTML element. Title extracted separately from body — never merged before scoring. Used independently for headline_bias parameter.</div></div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-n">4</div><div class="step-body"><div class="step-title">Keyword Extraction — for Cross-Feed Search Query</div><div class="step-desc">_extract_keywords(text, n=6): regex finds words ≥4 chars, removes 80-word stoplist, Counter.most_common(6) returns top keywords by frequency. These become the NewsAPI search query to find the same story from 8 other outlets.</div></div></div>
  </div>

