    <!-- 10 -->
    <div class="card" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')" style="padding:16px">
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:8px">
        <span style="font-size:20px">🏆</span>
        <div>
          <div style="font-size:9px;font-weight:800;color:var(--red);letter-spacing:.08em;margin-bottom:2px">ENHANCEMENT 10</div>
          <div class="card-title">Gamification Refinements</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:6px;margin-bottom:8px;flex-wrap:wrap">
        <span style="font-size:9px;padding:2px 7px;border-radius:4px;background:rgba(224,90,47,0.15);color:#f08060;font-weight:700">Current: points + streaks + leaderboard</span>
        <span style="font-size:9px;padding:2px 7px;border-radius:4px;background:rgba(27,173,135,0.15);color:#4BC8A0;font-weight:700">→ Progress bars + quizzes + social share</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-sub">Weekly challenges, peer percentile comparisons, post-article quizzes, and unpredictable bonus rewards sustain long-term engagement.</div>
      <div class="card-detail">
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.8">
          <strong style="color:#fff">→</strong> Progress bars per badge ("X more analyses to unlock Expert Analyst")<br>
          <strong style="color:#fff">→</strong> Weekly challenges ("Analyze 5 climate stories this week")<br>
          <strong style="color:#fff">→</strong> Peer percentile: "You are in top 10% of analysts this week"<br>
          <strong style="color:#fff">→</strong> Post-article mini-quiz: earn extra points for spotting biases<br>
          <strong style="color:#fff">→</strong> Social sharing of comparison charts (anonymized) for viral reach<br>
          <strong style="color:#fff">→</strong> Unpredictable bonus rewards (psychology: variable ratio schedule)<br>
          <strong style="color:#fff">→</strong> Monitor which rewards correlate with continued usage (opt-in analytics)<br>
          <strong style="color:#fff">Goal:</strong> Educational platform, not just a tool — reward critical reading practice
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- Validation summary -->
  <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(123,115,224,0.08),rgba(42,139,224,0.05));border:1px solid rgba(123,115,224,0.25);border-radius:14px;padding:18px 20px;margin-top:8px">
    <div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent);letter-spacing:.08em;margin-bottom:10px">PROTOTYPE VALIDATION — KEY RESULTS</div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:10px">
      <div style="text-align:center;padding:10px;background:rgba(27,173,135,0.07);border:1px solid rgba(27,173,135,0.18);border-radius:9px">
        <div style="font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#4BC8A0;margin-bottom:4px">↓ Errors</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2)">BERT + Louvain clustering yielded significantly fewer mis-grouped stories vs title-only TF-IDF</div>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align:center;padding:10px;background:rgba(123,115,224,0.07);border:1px solid rgba(123,115,224,0.18);border-radius:9px">
        <div style="font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:rgba(180,175,240,0.9);margin-bottom:4px">GPT Align</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2)">GPT-4 political lean prompts showed good alignment against known outlet bias ratings</div>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align:center;padding:10px;background:rgba(42,139,224,0.07);border:1px solid rgba(42,139,224,0.18);border-radius:9px">
        <div style="font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#5aafec;margin-bottom:4px">JS &gt; σ²</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text2)">Jensen–Shannon divergence highlighted contentious stories more sharply than plain variance</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top:10px;font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.7">
      Learned scoring weights on small annotated sets yielded more intuitive results — opinion pieces ranked higher in bias than neutral reports. Linking SHAP bars to phrases greatly improved understanding of model decisions. Each change validated iteratively against ground-truth event clusters and human judgment.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="badge-row" style="margin-top:16px">
    <div class="badge-label">Proposed</div>
    <div class="badges"><span class="badge">Apache Airflow</span><span class="badge">Louvain clustering</span><span class="badge">all-mpnet-base-v2</span><span class="badge">RoBERTa clickbait</span><span class="badge">GPT-4 lean classifier</span><span class="badge">JS-divergence</span><span class="badge">NRC Emotion Lexicon</span><span class="badge">TTL cache</span><span class="badge">SHAP phrase highlight</span></div>
  </div>
